A host of changes are looming to boost our ailing economy when South Africa’s lockdown is eased to Level Four. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A host of changes are looming to boost our ailing economy when South Africa’s lockdown is eased to Level Four. People will have to wear masks in public, deliveries from restaurants will be allowed, and you can exercise but under strict conditions yet to be announced. WATCH: Government provides update on level 4 restrictions No more than three people are allowed in private cars, and there’s a 70-percent operational capacity for public transport. A curfew will be in place from 8pm to 5am. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs. Permitted Goods Services an... by eNCA.com on Scribd 